    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the world's largest religious monument, built by the Khmer Empire as a Hindu (later Buddhist) temple.",
    history: "Built in the 12th century by King Suryavarman II, spanning 162.6 hectares with a moat 190 metres wide. It is the best preserved Khmer temple, aligned with sunrise at equinox. Its image appears on Cambodia's national flag.",
