    city: "Magelang",
    country: "Indonesia",
    latitude: -7.6079,
    longitude: 110.2038,
    category: "Temple",
    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the world's largest Buddhist temple, a 9th-century mandala-shaped monument with 504 Buddha statues and 2,672 relief panels.",
    history: "Built around 800 CE during the Sailendra dynasty. Abandoned and covered by volcanic ash and jungle for centuries, it was rediscovered in 1814 by Dutch colonists under Sir Thomas Stamford Raffles. It represents the Buddhist cosmological universe.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8c/Borobudur-Nothwest-view.jpg/800px-Borobudur-Nothwest-view.jpg"
