    history: "Built in 1395 as the main royal palace of the Joseon Dynasty. Destroyed by the Japanese in 1592, rebuilt by Regent Heungseon Daewongun in 1867. The Japanese colonial government demolished 90% of the buildings. Restoration has been ongoing since 1990.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Gyeongbokgung_Palace.jpg/800px-Gyeongbokgung_Palace.jpg"
