    latitude: 12.0317,
    longitude: 39.0471,
    category: "Monument",
    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, eleven monolithic churches carved from solid rock in the 12th century, still active places of worship for Ethiopian Orthodox Christians.",
    history: "Built by King Lalibela around 1200 CE as a 'New Jerusalem' after the Muslim capture of the Holy City. The churches are carved top-down from the rock, connected by tunnels and trenches. Bete Giyorgis (Church of St George) is the most iconic.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/00/Bet_Giyorgis%2C_Lalibela_01.jpg/800px-Bet_Giyorgis%2C_Lalibela_01.jpg"
