    longitude: 30.9338,
    category: "Ruins",
    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the ruins of a medieval city that was the capital of the Kingdom of Zimbabwe between the 11th and 15th centuries.",
    history: "Built between the 11th and 15th centuries by the Shona people using dry-stone walling with no mortar. At its peak it had a population of 18,000. The Great Enclosure has a wall 11 metres high and 5 metres thick. It gave its name to the country of Zimbabwe.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/28/Great_Zimbabwe_Closeup.jpg/800px-Great_Zimbabwe_Closeup.jpg"
