    description: "The mortuary temple of Queen Hatshepsut, one of ancient Egypt's most powerful female pharaohs, carved into a dramatic cliff face across the Nile from Luxor.",
    history: "Built around 1479–1458 BCE by Senenmut, Hatshepsut's chief steward and architect. After her death, Thutmose III tried to erase her memory by destroying her images. The temple was used by early Christians as a monastery, giving it the name 'Monastery of the North'.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6a/Hatshepsut_mortuary_temple.jpg/800px-Hatshepsut_mortuary_temple.jpg"
