    latitude: 16.7987,
    longitude: 96.1497,
    category: "Temple",
    description: "A 98-metre gilded stupa said to enshrine hairs of the Gautama Buddha and relics of three previous Buddhas, the most sacred Buddhist pagoda in Myanmar.",
    history: "Believed to be 2,600 years old, making it the oldest Buddhist stupa in the world, though historians date the current structure to the 14th century. The stupa is gilded with real gold: over 60 tons of gold. The tip is encrusted with 5,448 diamonds.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b8/Shwedagon_Pagoda_at_Dusk.jpg/800px-Shwedagon_Pagoda_at_Dusk.jpg"
