    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the Chinese imperial palace from the Ming Dynasty, the world's largest collection of preserved ancient wooden structures.",
    history: "Built between 1406 and 1420, the palace has 980 buildings over 72 hectares. It served as home of Chinese emperors for 500 years (1420–1912). The name refers to the fact that no one could enter or leave without the emperor's permission.",
