    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the finest surviving example of Japanese castle architecture, also called Hakuro-jo (White Heron Castle) for its brilliant white exterior.",
    history: "The main tower was built in 1601 by Ikeda Terumasa. It survived WWII bombing raids — a direct hit failed to explode. The castle system spans 83 buildings across a complex defensive layout. It has been used as a film location for numerous Japanese films.",
