    category: "Temple",
    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, a 9th-century Hindu temple compound dedicated to the Trimurti (Brahma, Vishnu, Shiva) with 240 temples in total.",
    history: "Built around 850 CE by the Sanjaya Dynasty. The Shiva temple rises 47 metres. The complex was abandoned after a volcanic eruption and earthquake in the 10th century. A massive earthquake in 2006 damaged many restored temples. The annual Ramayana ballet is performed against its backdrop.",
