    category: "Ruins",
    description: "A UNESCO World Heritage Site, the ruins of the great Phoenician city that was a major power in the ancient Mediterranean before being destroyed by Rome.",
    history: "Founded around 814 BCE by Phoenicians from Tyre, Carthage became the dominant power in the western Mediterranean. It fought three Punic Wars against Rome. After the Third Punic War (149–146 BCE), Rome razed the city entirely. Archaeological remains include baths, villas, and the Tophet sanctuary.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Baths_of_Antoninus%2C_Carthage%2C_Tunisia.jpg/800px-Baths_of_Antoninus%2C_Carthage%2C_Tunisia.jpg"
