    city: "Ubud",
    country: "Indonesia",
    latitude: -8.573,
    longitude: 115.2972,
    category: "Waterfall",
    description: "Tegenungan Falls is a picturesque waterfall near Ubud in Bali, where the Petanu River cascades about 20 meters into a wide pool surrounded by lush tropical greenery.",
    history: "Located just 20 minutes from Ubud, Tegenungan is one of Bali's most accessible waterfalls. While small by global standards, its beautiful setting and clear swimming pool have made it one of Bali's most photographed natural attractions.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Tegenungan_Waterfall_in_Bali.jpg/800px-Tegenungan_Waterfall_in_Bali.jpg"
