    longitude: 86.925,
    category: "Mountain Peak",
    description: "Mount Everest is the highest point on Earth at 8,848.86 meters above sea level, standing on the border of Nepal and Tibet. The summit lies in the death zone where oxygen levels are insufficient to sustain human life, yet thousands of climbers have reached the top since its first ascent in 1953.",
    history: "Known as Sagarmatha in Nepali and Chomolungma in Tibetan, meaning 'Goddess Mother of the World,' Everest was surveyed and named after British surveyor Sir George Everest in 1865. Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay made the first confirmed ascent on May 29, 1953. Over 300 people have died on the mountain; their bodies remain frozen in place.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e7/Everest_North_Face_toward_Base_Camp_Tibet_Luca_Galuzzi_2006.jpg/800px-Everest_North_Face_toward_Base_Camp_Tibet_Luca_Galuzzi_2006.jpg"
