    category: "Mountain Peak",
    description: "The Matterhorn is one of the most recognizable mountains in the world, its perfect four-sided pyramid rising 4,478 meters above Zermatt. It stands alone on the Swiss-Italian border and is one of the deadliest mountains in the Alps, having claimed over 500 lives since the first ascent in 1865.",
    history: "First climbed by Edward Whymper's team in 1865 in a tragic expedition where four climbers died on the descent in what became one of mountaineering's most famous disasters. The mountain was the inspiration for the Toblerone chocolate logo. Approximately 3,000 climbers attempt the summit each year.",
    imageUrl: "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/16/The_Matterhorn_from_Domh%C3%BCtte_-_2012-06.jpg/800px-The_Matterhorn_from_Domh%C3%BCtte_-_2012-06.jpg"
