    history: "Kempty Falls was developed as a picnic spot by John Mekinon, a British officer, in 1835. The name 'Kempty' is believed to be derived from 'Camp-Tea,' as British officers used to camp here for evening tea parties. The falls have since become one of Uttarakhand's most visited natural attractions and are accessible by road from Mussoorie.",
