    history: "Nihargarh Fort was constructed by the Scindia dynasty in the 18th century as a strategic outpost in the Vindhya range. The fort served as a defensive fortification and watchtower during the Maratha period. It later came under British influence during the colonial era and has since been recognized as a heritage site of historical importance in Madhya Pradesh.",
