    description: "Bhangarh Fort is a 17th-century fort in the Alwar district of Rajasthan, India, renowned as one of the most haunted places in India. Set in the Aravalli Range, the fort complex includes temples, havelis, and a palace, and is famous for its eerie atmosphere and the legends of curses that surround it.",
    history: "Bhangarh Fort was built in 1613 by Madho Singh I, a younger brother of Man Singh I of Amber, as a gift to his son Ajab Singh. According to local legend, a sorcerer named Singhia cursed the fort after his advances were rejected by the princess Ratnavati, leading to the destruction of the kingdom. The fort was abandoned after a battle in 1783 and has remained in ruins ever since. The Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) maintains the site but prohibits entry after sunset due to its supernatural reputation.",
